Package: minicom
Version: 2.00.0
Revision: 3
BuildDepends: automake
Recommends: lrzsz, ckermit
Source: http://www.netsw.org/net/modem/terminal/%n-%v.src.tar.gz
SourceDirectory: %n
Patch: %f.patch
ConfigureParams: --enable-lock-dir=%p/var/run --enable-dfl-port=/dev/cu.modem --mandir='${prefix}/share/man' --infodir='${prefix}/share/info'
DocFiles: ABOUT-NLS AUTHORS COPYING ChangeLog changelog.fink INSTALL NEWS README doc/*
CompileScript: <<
cp $p/share/automake-1.6/config.guess aux
cp $p/share/automake-1.6/config.sub aux
cp $p/share/automake-1.6/install-sh aux
cp $p/share/automake-1.6/missing aux
cp $p/share/automake-1.6/mkinstalldirs aux
./configure %c
make
<<
Description: Serial communication program
DescDetail: <<
Minicom is a serial communication program. It is a Unix clone of the well-known MS-DOS Telix program. It has ANSI color, a dialing directory, dial-a-list, and a scripting language.
<<
DescPort: <<
Had to update getopt.c and for the compile of getopt_long.c. Also had to update the Makefile to fix install locations. Changed z/y/zmodem default locations, and other default configs.
<<
